        <abstract>
            <p>Responds to CD’s comments on his MS on phyllotaxy.</p>
            <p>The initial variation required by his theory would be a slight twist of the bud-axis; believes the frequent twisting of stems and branches renders such a variation possible.</p>
            <p>Admits he placed too much emphasis on the importance of frost. He should have spoken more generally of "vicissitudes of climate".</p>
        </abstract>
